mediaNotes:
This cut begins with a decapitated chorus by a single bird that we saw perched in the open about 60 meters away and high up in a tall, dead snag at the edge of terra firme forest along the spur road about 1 1/4 km. beyond the logging camp. 

The bird was essentially silent (though it may have called softly once or twice) in the second part of this recording, when I was perched about 50 meters away in 35 meters up in a fully leafed tree. The bird shifted positions again before the third part of this recording, when it was unseen but apparently about 35 meters away and 30 meters off the ground. Partly cloudy, intermittent breeze, 78° F. Equipment Notes: Sennheiser powered using phantom power and with filter in flat position and attenuator off for all recordings.  Nagra input set at 2 mV / Pa and low-pass filter in flat position unless noted otherwise.
